# Phase 4: Manuscript UI Redesign & Demo Flow

> **Goal:** Transform Quill from the current dark SaaS theme into the editorial, manuscript-inspired design system defined in [design.md](file:///home/daikyri/Workspace/Hackathon-QwenCloud/design.md) — matching your mockup examples exactly.

---

## Design System Summary (from design.md)

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| **Ink** | `#292919` |
| **Paper** | `#F7F7EE` |
| **Typography** | Serif titles (editorial), clean body, marginal notes for microcopy |
| **Surfaces** | Paper textures with subtle grain, cards as manuscript pages, sidebar as ink/leather |
| **Buttons** | Outline or ink-filled, hover = "inking" effect |
| **Inputs** | Underlined style, writing animation on focus |
| **Animations** | GSAP + ScrollTrigger, slow/organic, fade + vertical reveal, SVG ink drawing |
| **Illustrations** | Black & white, engraving/sketch style, no color |
| **Rule** | No new colors — use opacity variations of Ink and Paper only |

